<item>
            <title>[LU-18609] use of logical &apos;&amp;&amp;&apos; with constant operand</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18609</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;the latest report on new defect(s) introduced to Lustre found with Coverity Scan.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;CID 454269:    (CONSTANT_EXPRESSION_RESULT)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;/lustre/osc/osc_cache.c: 2048 in get_read_extents()&lt;br/&gt;
   CID 454269:    (CONSTANT_EXPRESSION_RESULT)&lt;br/&gt;
   The expression &quot;!!ldlm_lock_to_ns(__ext-&amp;gt;oe_dlmlock)-&amp;gt;ns_dump_stack_on_error &amp;amp;&amp;amp; 1 /* D_ERROR &amp;amp; D_ERROR */&quot; is suspicious because it performs a Boolean operation on a constant other than 0 or 1.&lt;br/&gt;
2048             EASSERT(ext-&amp;gt;oe_nr_pages &amp;lt;= data.erd_max_pages, ext);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Some new gcc would report warning: use of logical &apos;&amp;amp;&amp;amp;&apos; with constant operand &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;-Wconstant-logical-operand&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
